reviews.review: Not sure why everyone is hating on this movie. It was a fun movie and wrapped up the story nicely. It did seem to be fast and jump all over but that made for a very exciting movie to me.
Went a long way towards helping me to get over there awful nonsense that was The Last Jedi. Not perfect but miles closer than episode 8.

It gave the respect it deserved to every character throughout the whole Saga. The time lapse for the development of the story could have been less rushed at times but I thing the director did the right thing to correct the horrible mistakes made in the previous movie. I loved it. And it touched the feelings of every fan of the SW universe.
It explained a lot but it also left question. Over best one of the new Trilogy

If you are a Star Wars fan, you will find this film very gratifying.  Yes, the story has been told before, but aren't we all just watching the same hero's journey with most movies?  It works, because the themes and archetypes resonate deep within our collective unconscious.

Surprised at how wrong the critics have been with this. I love the pace, the action and characters. The last movie left me empty, this one gave me excitement, fun and some closure( although I want more).
The film is very rushed and sloppy.

Once again, critic scores are meaningless. Not a perfect movie, but a perfect Star Wars movie. Yes there is fan service, but who are these movies made for of not the fans? It's a good movie with a logical story, that tries to unravel the mess made by its predecessor and has great character moments with an ultimately satisfying conclusion.

I am old enough that I saw A New Hope in the theater back in 1977, and have been a Star Wars fan since I was about 4 years old.  So I have been waiting for 42 years for the final film in the original storyline. This movie was FANTASTIC!  Well worth the 42 year wait.  I've never cried so much during a Star Wars movie as I did with Rise of Skywalker. I even have male friends who admitted they cried as well. The twists and turns are amazing. Definitely will go see it again.
